FORMAT: 1A

# book management system

API for book management

### /books

#### Create book [POST]

Create new book

+ Request (application/json)

    Details of the book to be created.

    + Attributes

    + Body

            {
              "title": "",
              "author": 0,
              "description": "",
              "numOfPages": 0,
              "year": 0
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    Book create successfully

    + Attributes

    + Body

            {
              "id": 0,
              "title": "",
              "author": {
                "id": 0,
                "name": "",
                "birth": 0,
                "numOfBooks": 0
              },
              "description": "",
              "numOfPages": 0,
              "year": 0,
              "cover": {}
            }

+ Request (application/json)

    Details of the book to be created.

    + Attributes

    + Body

            {
              "title": "",
              "author": 0,
              "description": "",
              "numOfPages": 0,
              "year": 0
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    The server could not understand the request due to invalid syntax. The client should modify the request and try again.

    + Attributes (required)

    + Body

            {
              "message": ""
            }

#### Get book list [GET /books{?title,author_id,page}]

Get book list by pages

+ Parameters

    + title - To filter book by title

    + author_id - To filter book by author id

    + page (required) - page

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    A JSON array containing book objects.

    + Attributes

    + Body

            [
              {
                "id": 0,
                "title": "",
                "author": {
                  "id": 0,
                  "name": "",
                  "birth": 0,
                  "numOfBooks": 0
                },
                "description": "",
                "numOfPages": 0,
                "year": 0,
                "cover": {}
              }
            ]

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    The server could not understand the request due to invalid syntax. The client should modify the request and try again.

    + Attributes (required)

    + Body

            {
              "message": ""
            }

+ Response 500 (application/json)

    The server encountered an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request. Report the issue to the support team if it persists.

    + Attributes (required)

    + Body

            {
              "message": ""
            }

### /books/{book_id}

#### Get book [GET]

Get book by id

+ Parameters

    + book_id (required) - Path parameter to retrieve books by.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    A JSON object containing the book details.

    + Attributes

    + Body

            {
              "id": 0,
              "title": "",
              "author": {
                "id": 0,
                "name": "",
                "birth": 0,
                "numOfBooks": 0
              },
              "description": "",
              "numOfPages": 0,
              "year": 0,
              "cover": {}
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    The server could not understand the request due to invalid syntax. The client should modify the request and try again.

    + Attributes (required)

    + Body

            {
              "message": ""
            }

